[6] Cholera - Ghana (northern regions)
Date: Fri 26 Aug 2011
Source: Modern Ghana [edited]
http://www.modernghana.com/news/347333/1/cholera-alert-in-northern-regions.html


The Ghana Health Service (GHS) is raising cholera alerts in some parts
of the country, especially the 3 northern regions, as the rains
continue to fall.

There are already reports of an outbreak of cholera in some parts of
the Brong Ahafo region which has claimed one life.

Meanwhile, 25 new cholera cases have been reported at the Kwesimintsim
Polyclinic in the Sekondi/Takoradi Metropolis.

Dr Jonathan Mensah, acting medical superintendent of the hospital,
told the Ghana News Agency that 2 deaths had so far been recorded.

