[7] Cholera - Ghana (Brong Ahafo Region)
Date: Sun 14 Aug 2011
Source: Ghana News Agency [edited]
http://www.ghananewsagency.org/details/Health/Cholera-outbreak-suspected-at-Atebubu-Amantin-District-/?ci=1&ai=32379


The Atebubu-Amantin District Directorate of Ghana Health Service says
it suspects an outbreak of cholera in the district following
increasing diarrhea cases reported at health facilities. A man
believed to be in his 50s recently died of the disease in the area.

Mr Ramseyer Ahmed, Atebubu-Amantin District disease control officer,
announced that from January to August 2011, a total number of 814
diarrhea cases had been recorded by the health directorate. The
majority of the cases were reported from Atebubu-Zongo and
Atebubu-Konkomba Line communities, he added.

